<subSubSection id="C35678CBFF97FF82FF7BF9E360B0A9C5" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF32B40FF97FF82FF7BF9E360B0A9C5" blockId="6.[151,1437,1636,2022]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B938F752FF97FF82FF7BF9E36262A97D" bold="true" box="[151,266,1636,1661]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Postgenal and antepronotal setae weaker than dorsal thoracic setae. Thorax and legs predominantly yellow. Abdomen shinning black. Male wing infuscated at apex; female wing infuscated at costal margin. Flagellum short pilose. Posterior tibia with long setae. Hypandrium distinctly wider at apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35678CBFF97FF83FF25F957603CA8BB" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF32B40FF97FF83FF25F9576003AD87" blockId="6.[151,1437,1636,2022]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,151,647]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B938F752FF97FF82FF25F957623CA9E9" bold="true" box="[201,340,1744,1769]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Description</emphasis>
. 
<typeStatus id="54F795E2FF97FF82FE8DF95762A1A9E8" box="[353,457,1744,1768]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Holotype</typeStatus>
male. Body length 3.0 mm; wing length 3.9 mm. Head with frons shining black, as large as anterior ocellus width. Face less shining black, as wide as frons, slightly gray pruinose at apex. Ocellar tubercle slightly protuberant with 
<number id="3D843967FF97FF82FE5FF89F62A9A830" box="[435,449,1816,1840]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="2.0">2</number>
pairs of ocellar setae, posterior pair minute. Postcranium black, gray pruinose. Antenna velvety black with pedicel yellowish. Flagellum pubescent, with 
<number id="3D843967FF97FF82FC9CF8BA6016A855" box="[880,894,1853,1877]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="3.0">3</number>
flagellomeres. Proboscis yellow, brown at base. Palpus light brown to yellow. Thorax shining yellow with scutum and scutellum darker with more distinct gray pruinescence. Postpronotal and postalar lobes yellow. Depending on light incidence, in anterior view scutum with wide, dark stripe or 
<number id="3D843967FF97FF82FE9AF82F62ECA8C0" box="[374,388,1960,1984]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="2.0">2</number>
narrow dark stripes between dorsocentral setae. Thoracic setae: 
<number id="3D843967FF97FF82FBB8F82F670AA8C0" box="[1108,1122,1960,1984]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="4.0">4</number>
dorsocentrals with posterior stronger; 
<number id="3D843967FF97FF82FEECF84A6266A8E5" box="[256,270,1997,2021]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="3.0">3</number>
postpronotals with 
<number id="3D843967FF97FF82FE02F84A6294A8E5" box="[494,508,1997,2021]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="1.0">1</number>
longer; 
<number id="3D843967FF97FF82FDB5F84A610FA8E5" box="[601,615,1997,2021]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="3.0">3</number>
notopleurals with posterior stronger; 
<number id="3D843967FF97FF82FBFFF84A6749A8E5" box="[1043,1057,1997,2021]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="2.0">2</number>
pairs of scutellars with inner pair slightly convergent; 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FE97FF1062E1AFAF" box="[379,393,151,175]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="4.0">4</number>
antepronotals; 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FDD7FF10610DAFAF" box="[571,613,151,175]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
proepisternals; 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FCF2FF106044AFAF" box="[798,812,151,175]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="6.0">6</number>
katatergitals with anterior row stronger; other setae as described for 
<taxonomicName id="4C4C50C3FF96FF83FED9FF3B62D0AFD4" box="[309,440,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbipennis">
<emphasis id="B938F752FF96FF83FED9FF3B62D0AFD4" box="[309,440,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">limbipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group (diagnosed above). Legs shining yellow with apices of hind femur, fore tibia and mid tibia darker. 
<collectingCountry id="F35B6BD0FF96FF83FE51FF58629DAFF7" box="[445,501,223,247]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia and all tarsi black with fore tarsomeres 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FC02FF58677FAFF7" box="[1006,1047,223,247]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
white distally. Femora/tibiae setae slightly stronger: fore tibia (
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF96FF83FE34FE836143AE1C" box="[472,555,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 38" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[260,1326,707,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[259,1328,702,1626]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 38. Macrostomus nitidus, sp. nov. 32 – 35, paratype male from Goiás, Brazil; 32, left fore leg, posterior view; 33, left mid leg, anterior view; 34, right hind leg, anterior view; 35, wing; 36 – 38, holotype male; 36, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 37, terminalia, lateral view; 38, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Scales: 32 – 34 = 0.5 mm; 36 – 38 = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281637/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FDE2FE836143AE1C" box="[526,555,260,284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="32.0">32</number>
</figureCitation>
) with 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FD9AFE8361ECAE1C" box="[630,644,260,284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
anterodorsal seta near base, 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FC21FE8360B3AE1C" box="[973,987,260,284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
posterior near middle; mid femur (
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF96FF83FA82FE8363DCAE3F" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 38" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[260,1326,707,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[259,1328,702,1626]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 38. Macrostomus nitidus, sp. nov. 32 – 35, paratype male from Goiás, Brazil; 32, left fore leg, posterior view; 33, left mid leg, anterior view; 34, right hind leg, anterior view; 35, wing; 36 – 38, holotype male; 36, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 37, terminalia, lateral view; 38, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Scales: 32 – 34 = 0.5 mm; 36 – 38 = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281637/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FF7BFEA063DCAE3F" box="[151,180,295,319]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="33.0">33</number>
</figureCitation>
) with 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FEE9FEA0627BAE3F" box="[261,275,295,319]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
strong anterior seta near apex; mid tibia with 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FCD3FEA06025AE3F" box="[831,845,295,319]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="2.0">2</number>
anterodorsals, 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FBECFEA06742AE3F" box="[1024,1066,295,319]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
posterior along basal half, 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FA9EFEA066F4AE3F" box="[1394,1436,295,319]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
anteroventral at middle of distal half; hind femur (
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF96FF83FD24FECB6071AE64" box="[712,793,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 38" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[260,1326,707,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[259,1328,702,1626]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 38. Macrostomus nitidus, sp. nov. 32 – 35, paratype male from Goiás, Brazil; 32, left fore leg, posterior view; 33, left mid leg, anterior view; 34, right hind leg, anterior view; 35, wing; 36 – 38, holotype male; 36, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 37, terminalia, lateral view; 38, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Scales: 32 – 34 = 0.5 mm; 36 – 38 = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281637/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FD10FECB6071AE64" box="[764,793,332,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
) with 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FC8DFECB6007AE64" box="[865,879,332,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="2.0">2</number>
anterior setae, 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FBF6FECB6740AE64" box="[1050,1064,332,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
at basal fifth and 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FB1DFECB6797AE64" box="[1265,1279,332,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
at distal fifth, 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FF7BFEE863CDAE87" box="[151,165,367,391]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
stronger anteroventral at base of distal third, and other slender anteroventral setae; hind tibia with 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FAF4FEE8662AAE87" box="[1304,1346,367,391]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
slender dorsal setae. 
<collectingCountry id="F35B6BD0FF96FF83FEC1FE13620DAEAC" box="[301,357,404,428]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Hind</collectingCountry>
tarsomere 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FE0AFE13629CAEAC" box="[486,500,404,428]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
with 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FDD5FE13612FAEAC" box="[569,583,404,428]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
longer dorsal and short spine-like setae ventrally. Wing (
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF96FF83FB31FE136659AEAC" box="[1245,1329,404,428]" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 38" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[260,1326,707,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[259,1328,702,1626]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 38. Macrostomus nitidus, sp. nov. 32 – 35, paratype male from Goiás, Brazil; 32, left fore leg, posterior view; 33, left mid leg, anterior view; 34, right hind leg, anterior view; 35, wing; 36 – 38, holotype male; 36, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 37, terminalia, lateral view; 38, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Scales: 32 – 34 = 0.5 mm; 36 – 38 = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281637/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FAF8FE136659AEAC" box="[1300,1329,404,428]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="35.0">35</number>
</figureCitation>
) hyaline, brown infuscated at distal margin. Cell dm truncate. Veins M 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FCA8FE406024AED5" box="[836,844,455,469]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
, M 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FC9FFE406013AED5" box="[883,891,455,469]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="2.0">2</number>
and A 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FC2AFE4060A6AED5" box="[966,974,455,469]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
evanescent. Halter light yellow to white. Abdomen shining black with blue reflection in certain lights; lateral bristles longer. Sternites concolorous with tergites. Tergite 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FEF2FD856244AD1A" box="[286,300,514,538]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF96FF83FED0FD8562E5AD1A" box="[316,397,514,538]" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 38" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[260,1326,707,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[259,1328,702,1626]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 38. Macrostomus nitidus, sp. nov. 32 – 35, paratype male from Goiás, Brazil; 32, left fore leg, posterior view; 33, left mid leg, anterior view; 34, right hind leg, anterior view; 35, wing; 36 – 38, holotype male; 36, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 37, terminalia, lateral view; 38, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Scales: 32 – 34 = 0.5 mm; 36 – 38 = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281637/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FE9CFD8562E5AD1A" box="[368,397,514,538]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="36.0">36</number>
</figureCitation>
) with small projection inside median distal sinus. Epandrium (
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF96FF83FBA6FD8567F3AD1A" box="[1098,1179,514,538]" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 38" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[260,1326,707,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[259,1328,702,1626]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 38. Macrostomus nitidus, sp. nov. 32 – 35, paratype male from Goiás, Brazil; 32, left fore leg, posterior view; 33, left mid leg, anterior view; 34, right hind leg, anterior view; 35, wing; 36 – 38, holotype male; 36, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 37, terminalia, lateral view; 38, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Scales: 32 – 34 = 0.5 mm; 36 – 38 = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281637/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FB92FD8567F3AD1A" box="[1150,1179,514,538]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="37.0">37</number>
</figureCitation>
) with anterodorsal and posterodorsal lobes of same height with deep sinus. Anterior cercus very large with internal sinus; posterior cercus elongate; median lobe membranous with long setae. Hypandrium (
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF96FF83FC91FDCD60A5AD62" box="[893,973,586,610]" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 38" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[260,1326,707,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[259,1328,702,1626]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 38. Macrostomus nitidus, sp. nov. 32 – 35, paratype male from Goiás, Brazil; 32, left fore leg, posterior view; 33, left mid leg, anterior view; 34, right hind leg, anterior view; 35, wing; 36 – 38, holotype male; 36, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 37, terminalia, lateral view; 38, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Scales: 32 – 34 = 0.5 mm; 36 – 38 = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281637/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FC5CFDCD60A5AD62" box="[944,973,586,610]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="38.0">38</number>
</figureCitation>
) with many setae along posterior margin, with wider apex. Ejaculatory apodeme with short dorsal lamella.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF337BC8FF96FF83FF7BF9F666F4A9C5" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281637/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" targetBox="[260,1326,707,1623]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph id="8BF32B40FF96FF83FF7BF9F666F4A9C5" blockId="7.[151,1436,1649,1733]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B938F752FF96FF83FF7BF9F66224A987" bold="true" box="[151,332,1649,1672]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">FIGURES 32–38</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4C50C3FF96FF83FEB5F9F46144A988" box="[345,556,1650,1672]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B938F752FF96FF83FEB5F9F46144A988" box="[345,556,1650,1672]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Macrostomus 
<taxonomicName id="4C4C50C3FF96FF83FE0BF9F56144A988" box="[487,556,1650,1672]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" rank="species" species="nitidus" status="sp. nov.">nitidus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B938F752FF96FF83FDD4F9F561A6A987" bold="true" box="[568,718,1650,1672]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20B4A29FF96FF83FDD4F9F561E0A987" box="[568,648,1650,1671]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
32–35
</emphasis>
, paratype male from Goiás, Brazil; 
<emphasis id="B938F752FF96FF83FBDBF9F56738A987" bold="true" box="[1079,1104,1650,1671]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">32</emphasis>
, left fore leg, posterior view; 
<emphasis id="B938F752FF96FF83FA90F9F566FDA987" bold="true" box="[1404,1429,1650,1671]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">33</emphasis>
, left mid leg, anterior view; 
<emphasis id="B938F752FF96FF83FE5EF91662A3A9A6" bold="true" box="[434,459,1681,1702]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">34</emphasis>
, right hind leg, anterior view; 
<emphasis id="B938F752FF96FF83FCE5F916604AA9A6" bold="true" box="[777,802,1681,1702]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">35</emphasis>
, wing; 
<emphasis id="B938F752FF96FF83FC9EF91660D9A9A6" bold="true" box="[882,945,1681,1703]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">36–38</emphasis>
, holotype male; 
<emphasis id="B938F752FF96FF83FBB3F9166710A9A6" bold="true" box="[1119,1144,1681,1702]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">36</emphasis>
, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 
<emphasis id="B938F752FF96FF83FEC6F937622BA9C5" bold="true" box="[298,323,1712,1733]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">37</emphasis>
, terminalia, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B938F752FF96FF83FDAAF9376137A9C5" bold="true" box="[582,607,1712,1733]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">38</emphasis>
, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Scales: 32–34 = 0.5 mm; 36–38 = 0.2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BF32B40FF96FF83FF25F96A61CCA897" blockId="7.[151,1436,1773,2016]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Female. Body length 3.4 mm; wing length 3.7 mm. Frons and face wider than anterior ocellus width and wider than in male. Wing (
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF96FF83FE96F89662A2A829" box="[378,458,1809,1833]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="8.[151,264,816,839]" captionTargetBox="[260,1324,344,788]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[260,1327,339,791]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Macrostomus nitidus, sp. nov. paratype female from Goiás, Brazil; 39, wing; 40, tergite 8, 10 and cercus (cercus broken), dorsal view; 41, sternite 8, lateral view; 42, sternite 8, 10 and cercus (cercus broken), ventral view; 43, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 40 – 42 = 0.2 mm; 43 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281638/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FE41F89662A2A829" box="[429,458,1809,1833]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="39.0">39</number>
</figureCitation>
) with cell r 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FDA6F8A7613AA82E" box="[586,594,1824,1838]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
and base of cell r 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FCF9F8A76075A82E" box="[789,797,1824,1838]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FCCAF8A76045A82E" box="[806,813,1824,1838]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="3.0">3</number>
brown infuscated. Fore tarsi unicolorous. Tergite 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FAB8F896660AA829" box="[1364,1378,1809,1833]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF96FF83FA9CF89663DCA84F" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="8.[151,264,816,839]" captionTargetBox="[260,1324,344,788]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[260,1327,339,791]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Macrostomus nitidus, sp. nov. paratype female from Goiás, Brazil; 39, wing; 40, tergite 8, 10 and cercus (cercus broken), dorsal view; 41, sternite 8, lateral view; 42, sternite 8, 10 and cercus (cercus broken), ventral view; 43, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 40 – 42 = 0.2 mm; 43 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281638/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FF7BF8B063DCA84F" box="[151,180,1847,1871]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="40.0">40</number>
</figureCitation>
) with median and basal heavily sclerotized area. Sternite 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FCC8F8B0605AA84F" box="[804,818,1847,1871]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF96FF83FCACF8B060AFA84F" box="[832,967,1847,1871]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="8.[151,264,816,839]" captionTargetBox="[260,1324,344,788]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[260,1327,339,791]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Macrostomus nitidus, sp. nov. paratype female from Goiás, Brazil; 39, wing; 40, tergite 8, 10 and cercus (cercus broken), dorsal view; 41, sternite 8, lateral view; 42, sternite 8, 10 and cercus (cercus broken), ventral view; 43, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 40 – 42 = 0.2 mm; 43 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281638/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Figs. 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FC93F8B060AFA84F" box="[895,967,1847,1871]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="41.42">41, 42</number>
</figureCitation>
) distinctly curved with anterior third thinner, ventrally more sclerotized at median third. Tergite 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FCEAF8DC6049A873" box="[774,801,1883,1907]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="10.0">10</number>
with basal incision (
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF96FF83FBEAF8DC673EA873" box="[1030,1110,1883,1907]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="8.[151,264,816,839]" captionTargetBox="[260,1324,344,788]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[260,1327,339,791]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Macrostomus nitidus, sp. nov. paratype female from Goiás, Brazil; 39, wing; 40, tergite 8, 10 and cercus (cercus broken), dorsal view; 41, sternite 8, lateral view; 42, sternite 8, 10 and cercus (cercus broken), ventral view; 43, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 40 – 42 = 0.2 mm; 43 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281638/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FBD5F8DC673EA873" box="[1081,1110,1883,1907]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="40.0">40</number>
</figureCitation>
) [cerci broken]. Genital fork (
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF96FF83FF73F8F86398A897" box="[159,240,1919,1943]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="8.[151,264,816,839]" captionTargetBox="[260,1324,344,788]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[260,1327,339,791]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Macrostomus nitidus, sp. nov. paratype female from Goiás, Brazil; 39, wing; 40, tergite 8, 10 and cercus (cercus broken), dorsal view; 41, sternite 8, lateral view; 42, sternite 8, 10 and cercus (cercus broken), ventral view; 43, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 40 – 42 = 0.2 mm; 43 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281638/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF96FF83FF3FF8F86398A897" box="[211,240,1919,1943]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="43.0">43</number>
</figureCitation>
) small. Genital chamber membranous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF32B40FF96FF83FF25F824603CA8BB" blockId="7.[151,1436,1773,2016]" box="[201,852,1955,1980]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B938F752FF96FF83FF25F8246297A8BC" bold="true" box="[201,511,1955,1980]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Geographical distribution</emphasis>
